    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-02-08T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-02-08T12:00:00-05:00" n="13"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d13">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">501.<gloss target="#t_BC1">BC</gloss>
                    Atomic/2–849: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        United States Representative at the United Nations</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Austin</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-02-08T12:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 8, 1949—12 noon</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>64. 1. Only concern of Dept re early meeting <gloss target="#t_AEC1">AEC</gloss>
                    is that prior to formulation of formal US position on work of Commission, this
                    Govt might become committed to a position later found to be out of harmony with
                    US position.</p>
                <pb facs="0060" n="30" xml:id="pg_30"/>
                <p>2. If in your judgment interim program proposed by Osborn and McNaughton, namely,
                    publication of new booklet on plan, followed by clarification of
                    misunderstandings of plan expressed in <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss>, can be
                    carried through without prejudice to future program of Commission or
                    consultations you may in your discretion ask for early meeting of
                    Commission.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
